# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 1 (Foundation)

Full spec: `docs/02_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_01_FOUNDATION.md`

## Priority

1. Build Bible V2
2. Existing architecture
3. Existing implementation — change code when it conflicts with V2

## Non-negotiables

- No `TODO` / `FIXME` comments
- No placeholders, temporary fixes, or unfinished work
- No `any`, `@ts-ignore`, `@ts-nocheck` unless unavoidable and justified
- Business logic only in `src/lib/**` — not in presentation components
- Never import `@/lib/supabase/server` or `@/lib/supabase/admin` from Client Components
- API routes: no JSX / UI components
- Prefer Server Components; Client Components only when required
- RLS stays enabled; never weaken tenant isolation
- Never expose secrets to the client
- Preserve RBAC; do not widen or shrink roles accidentally
- **Paddle-only billing** — do not reintroduce Stripe runtime
- Stripe historical data is archive-only
- Money: `formatWorkspaceMoney` (CRM) / `formatMoneyFromCentsLocale` (billing cents)
- No destructive production-data migrations
- Before done: `npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`
